main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified objects in the sky over California and Oregon, reported during the evening of February 25, 1964.
interesting points: Witnesses described seeing 3 objects exploding with varying duration, some lasting 9-10 minutes,Two rockets were also reported launched southward during the same timeframe,In total, similarities were noted with six similar sightings within a short time,There were various descriptions of colors and light trails associated with the explosions,The investigation indicated potential explanations including balloons, astronomical phenomena, or aircraft, though data was deemed insufficient for a clear conclusion.
sighted object: three unidentified objects and two rockets
witness description: reports from military personnel including Lt Col Lucius Theus and various observers from Adair AFS
